{"questionId":"26717","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>The function&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>f</mi><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mi>ln</mi><mfenced><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></mfrac></mfenced></math>&nbsp;is defined for&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mo>&gt;</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>∈</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">ℝ</mi></math>.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Find an expression for <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi>f</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup><mo>(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>)</mo></math>. You are not required to state a domain.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>ln</mi><mfenced><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></mfrac></mfenced></math></p>\n<p>an attempt to isolate <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi></math> (or <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>y</mi></math> if switched)&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mtext>e</mtext><mi>y</mi></msup><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></mfrac></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>=</mo><msup><mtext>e</mtext><mrow><mo>-</mo><mi>y</mi></mrow></msup></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><msup><mtext>e</mtext><mrow><mo>-</mo><mi>y</mi></mrow></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn></math></p>\n<p>switching <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>y</mi></math> (seen anywhere)&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>M1</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi>f</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup><mo>(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>)</mo><mo>=</mo><msup><mtext>e</mtext><mrow><mo>-</mo><mi>x</mi></mrow></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn></math>&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<strong><em>A1</em></strong></p>\n<p><br><em><strong>[3 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"26717","referenceCode":"22M.1.AHL.TZ2.10a","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"Find an expression for f-1(x). You are not required to state a domain.","paper":"1","level":"HL","questionNumber":"a","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 3]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 2—Functions","Topic 2—Functions","AHL 2.7—Composite functions, finding inverse function incl domain restriction"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}